org.nasdanika.flow

Interface Participant

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Adaptable, EObject, Marked, ModelElement, NamedElement, Notifier, PackageElement<Participant>, ServiceProvider<Participant>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ParticipantImpl

    public interface Participant
extends ServiceProvider<Participant>
    A representation of the model object 'Participant'.

    The following features are supported:

    • Participates
    • Resources
    • Artifacts
    • Specializations
    • Base Keys
    • Bases
    • Responsible
    • Accountable
    • Consulted
    • Informed
    • Children
    See Also:
    FlowPackage.getParticipant()

    • Method Detail

      • getParticipates

        EList<FlowElement<?>> getParticipates()
        Returns the value of the 'Participates' reference list. The list contents are of type FlowElement<?>. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Participants'. Flow elements this participant participates in.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Participates' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Participates(), FlowElement.getParticipants()

      • getResources

        EList<Resource> getResources()
        Returns the value of the 'Resources' reference list. The list contents are of type Resource. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Used By'. Resources which this participant uses in their activities.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Resources' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Resources(), Resource.getUsedBy()

      • getBaseKeys

        EList<String> getBaseKeys()
        Returns the value of the 'Base Keys' attribute list. The list contents are of type String. Keys of base participants, which this participant is a specialization of, relative to the containing package ``participants/`` reference.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Base Keys' attribute list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_BaseKeys()

      • getBases

        EList<Participant> getBases()
        Returns the value of the 'Bases' reference list. The list contents are of type Participant. Base participants, which this participant is a specialization of. E.g. Junior Developer and Senior Developer can be specializations of Developer, which in turn can be a specialization of Agile Team Member.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Bases' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Bases()

      • getResponsible

        EList<ParticipantResponsibility<?>> getResponsible()
        Returns the value of the 'Responsible' reference list. The list contents are of type ParticipantResponsibility<?>. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Responsible'. Flow elements (activities, flows) this participant is responsible for, i.e. does the work to complete them. E.g. Product Owner is responsible for backlog grooming.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Responsible' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Responsible(), ParticipantResponsibility.getResponsible()

      • getAccountable

        EList<ParticipantResponsibility<?>> getAccountable()
        Returns the value of the 'Accountable' reference list. The list contents are of type ParticipantResponsibility<?>. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Accountable'. Flow elements (activities, flows) this participant is ultimately answerable for the correct and thorough completion.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Accountable' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Accountable(), ParticipantResponsibility.getAccountable()

      • getConsulted

        EList<ParticipantResponsibility<?>> getConsulted()
        Returns the value of the 'Consulted' reference list. The list contents are of type ParticipantResponsibility<?>. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Consulted'. Flow elements (activities, flows) for which this participant's opinions are sought, e.g. the participant is a subject-matter expert.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Consulted' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Consulted(), ParticipantResponsibility.getConsulted()

      • getInformed

        EList<ParticipantResponsibility<?>> getInformed()
        Returns the value of the 'Informed' reference list. The list contents are of type ParticipantResponsibility<?>. It is bidirectional and its opposite is 'Informed'. Flow elements (activities, flows) about which this participant is kept up-to-date on progress.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Informed' reference list.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Informed(), ParticipantResponsibility.getInformed()

      • getChildren

        EMap<String,Participant> getChildren()
        Returns the value of the 'Children' map. The key is of type String, and the value is of type Participant, Participants can be organized into a hierarchy (Organizational Structure).
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Children' map.
        See Also:
        FlowPackage.getParticipant_Children()
